<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Transport Select Committee:</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written e</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">vidence from the Department for Transport</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (SRN 008)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Introduction</span></p><ol type="i" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 12.66pt; padding-left:5.34pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">In June this year, the Chief Secretary to the Treasury announced </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Investing in Britain’s Future</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, unveiling</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">a transformational programme of investment in our strategic road network (SRN) worth up to £50 billion over the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">next</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> generation, including tripling spending on major road enhancements and resurfacing 80% of the network by 2021.</span></li><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 15.95pt; padding-left:2.05pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">This was followed in July by</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> the launch of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads: a network for the 21</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt; font-style:italic; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> century</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, in which we outlined our plans to transform the way in which we manage </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">England</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">’s </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. The plans, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">which we intend to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">underpin</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> by legislation, will see the Highways Agency turned into a publicly-owned company, with six-year funding certainty on</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">maintenance and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">improvement </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">work, from 2015 onwards.</span></li><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Taken together, these two documents are the most ambitious plans for roads in over </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">a generation. They represent a significant increase in the level of investment in our national roads infrastructure and a fundamental change in the way in which the network will be managed</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, which will </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">enable faster delivery, raise efficiency, improve trans</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">parency and unlock growth.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Questions</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.87pt; padding-left:9.13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How will the policies set out in the Government’s “Action for Roads” command paper improve the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> for all road users, whilst also improving the environment?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Investment</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The commitments </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">we </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">made in the Spending Review constitute the biggest ever upgrade of our </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">existing </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">strategic national roads network, tripling annual investment on major roads enhancements from today’s level to over £3bn by 2020/21.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">This </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">will allow us to address the backlog o</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">f repairs and deliver a world-class road network that can meet our future needs, transforming performance by </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">improving connectivity, capacity and journey reliability</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Investment can also enhance the standard of safety for road users. Our safest roads are t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">hose where we’ve already invested – where junctions are safe, where dual carriageways </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">and motorways </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">take much of the risk out of overtaking and where surfaces and alignments </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">reflect</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> modern</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> standards</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. For example improving </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">busy </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">at-grade junctions to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">grade-separated standard would not only mean better flowing traffic but potential safety improvements of 25%-50%.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">In </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">we made clear that a</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ny improvements to the network will need to be made in a way that supports our</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> quality of life and sustainability</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> outcomes. This means that our vision for roads must </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">e designed to minimise environmental impacts and also address existing problems. The scale of investment which we intend to deliver means that we can afford to invest </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">in environmental safeguards. Greater use of measures such as tunnels, green bridges, noise mitigation</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and measures to control air quality impacts</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, means that there </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">does not need to be </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">a stark choice between a well-functioning road network and a well-protec</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ted environment</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We will build on and expand existing cooperation with environmental and other </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">bodies</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">roads </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">investment </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">will </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">be accompanied by an aggressive policy of decarbonisation, to address the carbon consequences of motoring and move us to a lowe</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">r-impact future.  </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The Government has made an unprecedented long-term commitment to speeding the transition to low emission motoring in the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, including the goal of seeing every car on the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">’s roads effectively zero emission by 2050.  </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">committed an additional £500m to support the switch to the latest ultra-low emission vehicles</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">which builds upon existing funding and the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> £1 billion</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">of joint industry and g</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">overnment funding for an Advanced Propulsion Centre.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">This will </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">support</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">improvements</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> in air quality </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">as well as</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">reductions in</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> carbon </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">and greenhouse gas emissions</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We also want to ensure that improvements to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">take account of the needs of non-motorised users, such as cyclists and walkers. This includes addressing key areas where major</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> roads create a barrier to cyclists and walkers, improving safe access for cyclists, especially around junctions, and taking account of their needs in the design of road improvements. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The Highways Agency has </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">already </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">been working with Sustrans to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">identify s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">pecific</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> improvements </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">across the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> network. </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Reform</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Our strategic road network needs to be well-funded, with the right investment in the right places. However, it also needs to be well run in order to ensure that investment delivers value for money for</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">road users and taxpayers. </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.9.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> set out a range of significant reforms, building on the recommendations of Alan Cook’s 2011 </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">independent report ‘</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">A Fresh Start for the Strategic Road Network</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">to improve performance and efficiency. These included:</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#007662; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Reforming the </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Highways Agency</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> – turning the Agency into a publicly owned company will</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> allow the Agency to operate more like a commercial organisation, with freedom and flexibility over day-to-day operations and greater separation from government.</span></li><li style="color:#007662; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Long-te</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">rm </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">funding certainty</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">–</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">certainty of funding will overcome current problems of </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">stop-start funding, which constrains the ability of the Agency to plan ahead and secure efficiencies. Certainty</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">crucial for </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">giving the suppl</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">y</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> chain confidence to invest more in equipment and skills, and </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">get ready for the significant increase in </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">investment</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> over the next few years. Rising investment will mean more jobs and a stronger future for the construction industry in the </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="color:#007662; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">A Roads Investm</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ent Strategy</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> - setting out plans and performance criteria for </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">operations,</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> maintenance </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">and enhancements </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">to 2021 and beyond. We will produce the first Roads Investment Strategy later this Parliament.</span></li><li style="color:#007662; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 45.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Watchdog </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">- As part of the new framework, we intend to esta</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">blish a new road user watchdog to provide a strong voice for all road users, hold the new company to account and deliver effective scrutiny of delivery performance. This will result in more transparent</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> outcomes and outputs</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and improved value for money for </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">taxpayers and</span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> road users.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">1.10.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We expect these reforms to generate major efficiency savings across the roads programme. We will be launching a consultation on our more detailed proposals for reforming the Highways Agency in the near future.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.87pt; padding-left:9.13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How does the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Government’s policy for roads link with planning for other transport modes?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">It is important that transport planning is integrated with land use planning so that transport facilities can be developed to meet future needs at the outset. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">In May 2012 we set out </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">plans for </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">route based strategies (RBS</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">identify </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the management and enhancement </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">needs </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">of our road network</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> tak</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> account of local needs and interests</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, including</span><span style="fo