/span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Sheffield</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> will all be located close to existing motorways.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">2.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">epartment </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">has committed</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> to publish</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> a </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">National Networks </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">National Policy Statement (NN NPS) by the end of the year which will set</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> out the policy and planning framework within which applications for planning consent for nationally significant road, rail and rail freight interchange developments are considered. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">NN </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">NPS</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> will make an important contribution to removing planning barrie</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">rs to growth by providing clarity and certainty to scheme promoters and decision-makers on the government’s priorities for development.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.87pt; padding-left:9.13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How reliable is the Government’s forecast for growth in demand for the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">? How should the Government deal with uncerta</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">inty in its forecast? </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The N</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ational </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ransport </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">M</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">odel (NTM)</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> is designed to forecast long-term trends (currently 2010 to 2040 in five year intervals) based on:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#007662; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 46.37pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Our current understanding of how people make travel choices</span></li><li style="color:#007662; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 46.37pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The expected path of key drivers of </span><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">travel demand</span></li><li style="color:#007662; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 46.37pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#000000; font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Assuming no change in government policy beyond that already announced.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The three key drivers for road traffic are population, income and the costs</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> of road transport</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. Between 2010-2040 the population in </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">England</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> is expected to rise by 20%, GDP </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">per capita is projected to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">rise by 57% and the fuel cost of driving is projected to fall by 28%. By 2040 </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> traffic is forecast </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">(in the central case) </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">to be 46% higher than in 2010, implying an increase in congestion (measured</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">as lost time) of about 114%.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">B</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ackcasting exercise</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">s, which </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">input past economic and demographic drivers into the NTM accurately </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">support projections of</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> actual traffic growth on all roads in </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">England</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">give us confidence in our forecast</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">though we acknowledge that our model tends to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ov</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">erestimate traffic in urban areas (e.g. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">London</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">) and underestimate traffic in rural areas</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We continually work to update and improve our modelling and understanding on what and why something is happening and the impact on the future.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">3.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">However, u</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ncertainty is inherently part of forecasting and predicting future behaviour and trends. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">raffic trends and outcomes depend on a large number of variables, economic (</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">GDP</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, oil prices) and behavioural (people preferences, trends and social habits). </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Forecasts</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> must be interpreted as best estimates given </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">current state of</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">information and assumptions. We seek</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">reflect</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> this uncertainty by using </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">scenario analysis and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">sensitivity analysis to understand </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">impact</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> of different assumptions</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">a range of potentia</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">l alternative outcome</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">3.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We are exploring any changing patterns in the demand to travel, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">using the latest National Travel Survey (NTS) data</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">through the re-estimation of the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">trip rates</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, and the resultant number of trips to and from an area</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. These are</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> us</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ed in </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">our</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> National Transport Model (NTM) and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">also</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> feed into local roads schemes modelling and appraisal. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The first stage of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">project</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">addressing three key topics:</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 70.12pt; padding-left:1.58pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Should the existing trip rate values be modified?</span></li><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 70.39pt; padding-left:1.31pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Do trip rates vary over time?</span></li><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 69.17pt; padding-left:2.53pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Should </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">our model structure be modified?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">3.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The second stage of the trip rates project will further investigate the drivers behind any travel demand changes in trip rates observed from the first stage.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.87pt; padding-left:9.13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How can we improve the reliability and efficiency of travel on </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">? What impact will new technology have?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The Government has committed </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">a substantial increase in investment </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">on the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, which </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">will </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">help address long-term issues of capacity.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Much of the additional capacity </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">on the motorway network </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">will be provided through application of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">smart</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">motorways</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> (also known as ‘managed motorways’)</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. This is to help get the best out of some of the most con</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xad;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">gested sec</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xad;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">tions of our motor</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xad;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">way net</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xad;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">work. </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The Government will also </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">include</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> upgrade</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">s to</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> the national non</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">-motorway network managed by the H</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ighways </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">gency</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, with a </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">significant </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">proportion moved to dual-lane and grade-separated road ‘expressway’ standard to ensure free-flowing traffic nationwide. As part of this, the Government will tackle some of the most notori</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ous and long-standing road hot spots in the country. Roads which are widely recognised as being in need of a solution to alleviate congestion and tackle enduring problems.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The Government will identify and fund solutions, initially through feasibility studi</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">es, to look at problems and identify potential schemes on the A303 to the south west, the A27 on the south coast, the A1 north of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Newcastle</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, A1 Newcastle-Gateshead Western by-pass, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the A47 </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">and trans-Pennine routes between Sheffield and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Manchester</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Innovat</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ive technology</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">4.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Govern</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ment recognises the important role of technology </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">and information </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">in improving how people travel. Academia and industry are typically at the forefront of identifying the opportunities and challenges presented by new technologies, an</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">d in pushing the boundaries of what is possible. The role for Government is to provide the right environment and support to allow new technologies to flourish</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, including, for example,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">through sett</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">a clear</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> strategic vision and policy framework</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">removing </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">barriers to commercialisation</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, developing standards and bringing stakeholders together to address common issues</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The Department for Transport and the Highways Agency are already making effective use of innovative technologies to improve reliability, effici</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ency and safety</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> on the strategic roads for which they are responsible.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Following the success of the M42</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">smart motorway pilot scheme</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> -</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">which </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">dramatically improved safety</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">reliability of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">journeys, as well as reduced emissions and</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> noise -</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">overnment is</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">making a large scale commitment</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> to this technology. Of the 26 new Highways Agency national roads schemes due to start work by 2015, 13 are </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">smart </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">motorway schemes (see fig 2.4 in </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">). </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We have also provided funding to police forces in England</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> for 3D laser scanners to enable faster evidence capture by the police </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">following incidents, ensuring that lanes can be re-opened as soon as possible, minimising</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> disruption to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">road users</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and surrounding areas</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.9.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The Department for Transport and the Highways A</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">gency are also exploring the potential benefits and implications of</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">emerging technologies that will influence our roads in the future</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, as well as being closely involved in discussions at European level.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> A particular area of interest is ‘cooperative systems</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">’ where </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">vehicles cooperate with one another</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and/or the road infrastructure. </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.10.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">DfT has been working with researchers at </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Oxford</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">University</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and Nissan to develop a ground-breaking trial for semi-autonomous cars, ensuring that government legislation does</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> no</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">t bl</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ock innovation. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">DfT is </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">currently in the process of commissioning a feasibility study</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">to examine</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">potential benefits and impacts of </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">‘platooning’ for heavy vehicles on strategic roads,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and the possibility of UK trials</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">4.11.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Government’s plans for </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">reforming the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Highways </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">gency will </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">provide </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">greater freedom, flexibility and in</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">centives</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> for the SRN road operator </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">to develop innovative techniques to improve network management</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and deliver more efficiently</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; text-indent:-27pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.87pt; padding-left:9.13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What mechanisms are there for Government to </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">increase investment in strategic roads and attract new investors? Are there good examples from other countries that could be applied in the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">UK</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">? </span></li></ol><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">G</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">overnment is committed to investing in our national road infrastructure to improve capacity, reduce conges</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">tion and enhance connectivity across the country. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">In </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Investing in Britain’s Future</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, the Government outlined a dramatic increase in the level of public investment in infrastructure of all kinds, including roads. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">This will fund the biggest-ever upgrade of our existing network. </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">In delivering this investment, we will consider the ways in which the private sector can best help speed delivery and drive efficiency.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We continue to rule out tolls as a mechanism to fund</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> existing roads. However</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">here will be cases where the combination of the significant expense of the scheme and the distribution of the benefits means that it is fair that users meet some of the costs of the scheme, rather than general taxpayers. This wou</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ld be in very limited circumstances where schemes deliver new roads or transform an existing road into an entirely new route beyond all recognition and there is a strong economic and commercial case for a contribution from tolling.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">5.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">‘</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">’</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> has</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> set out the Government’s plans for reforming the Highways Agency, making it more efficient, more secure, and giving it the freedoms needed to match the best performance in the private sector. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">5.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">International experience, as well as lessons from the way oth</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">er types of infrastructure are run in the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, suggests that this could lead to more efficiency, quicker delivery and better forward planning.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">As discussed in ‘</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">’ </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">most European countries, such as </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">France</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Austria</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Sweden</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, run their </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">strategic roads at much greater distance from central government.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">5.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We are confident that our programme of reforms will allow </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">England</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">’s roads to catch up wit</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">h its international competitors</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. We will continue to keep </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the potential contribution of private finan</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ce</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> under review, but further institution</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">al change would only come after full </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">discussion </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">with the public and stakeholder groups. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12.6pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.87pt; padding-left:9.13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How should the Highways Agency be reformed</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">to make it “the world’s leading highway operator”? What roles should Government and</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> the private sector play to ensure better management of the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">6.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The management of the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> will always be a partnership between the network operator on the one hand and a range of private sector contractors on the other. Successful cooperation is vital to a well-run and cost-effective road network.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">6.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> transformation</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> to set up the Highways Agen</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">cy as a</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">publicly-owned company</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, as laid out in </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">’</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> is aligned with the recommendations made in </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">Alan Cook</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">’s independent </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">2011 </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">report </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">will</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">substantially improve the network operator’s performance</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">We will provide more details of the Governm</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ent’s proposals for reform of the Agency in our forthcoming consultation.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">6.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">These changes</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">represent</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> a clear break from </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">short-term thinking and stop-start culture</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> that has affected the management of the network to date</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">. It will put in place the structures</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, commitments and relationships to support a more ambitious infrastructure programme, and allow the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> to operate more like the best-performing infrastructure providers in other sectors. </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">6.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">It will mean a clearer, more strategic role for government – provid</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ing a strong, certain framework against which the managers of the </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">SRN</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> could be held to account, and a network operator who can prioritise network management over government processes. </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">6.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">This will have knock on benefits for suppliers. Credible independence </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">will allow confidence in road investment plans, enabling suppliers to procure materials at lower costs through longer contracts and invest more in recruitment and staff training.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">6.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">It will also challenge the supply sector. T</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">new body </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">will be seeking an exp</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">ansion in supply, cost savings and doing things faster</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">, which will bring new challenges to m</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">anufacturers and suppliers</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> We will need industry to step up to help us deliver our objective to have a road network fit for the 21</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> century.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Alan Cook</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">A Fresh Start for the Strategic Road Network</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">November </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">2011</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> ‘</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">trip rates</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> are the number of trips made by person segmented by area, household a</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">nd purpose of the journey</span></p></body></html>